Chief (Dr.) Christian Francis Ipoola Olaniyan, an accomplished educationist and proprietor of Victory Group of Schools in Lagos and Osun States has died. Olaniyan died on Tuesday, April 5, 2022 at a private hospital in Lagos at the age of 93. A professional teacher of repute, Olaniyan worked tirelessly to see that his dreams realised. Pa Olaniyan would be laid to rest at Ode-Omu in Osun State, Saturday 18, 2022, after a church service at Bola Memorial Anglican Church, Abule Onigbagbo, Ikeja on Friday 17, 2022. The burial holds June 17, 18 at Ode-Omu. He was educated in the famous school, Oduduwa College, Ile-Ife, Osun State; Fourah Bay College, Freetown, Sierra Leone, Durhan University Dublin in Ireland where he bagged Higher Diploma in Education, B.A. Hons (English, Latin Maths). He taught in many schools in Osun, Oyo and Lagos states as a Vice Principal and Principal. His last place of work, Oriwu College, Ikorodu as Principal. Pa Olaniyan inherited teaching profession from his late Father and mother. POLL Undaunted Pa Olaniyan established the first private school, Victory High School, Ikeja, in 1969 followed with other seven in Lagos and Osun States. In 1983, he was a Commissioner f o r Establishment and Training in old Oyo State under Dr. Omololu Olunloyo as governor, while his government was truncated in December the same year. The deceased was honoured with many awards, traditional titles both in Lagos and Osun states. He was once President of Ikeja Club and many other notable organizations. He spent his wealth on churches and organisations. He was a former Director of Bank of Commerce and Industry and others. He is survived with wives, children, grandchildren and great-grandchildren.